{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "I am the man who has seen affliction by the rod of the Lord's wrath.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has driven me away and made me walk in darkness rather than light;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "indeed, he has turned his hand against me again and again, all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has made my skin and my flesh grow old and has broken my bones."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has besieged me and surrounded me with bitterness and hardship."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has made me dwell in darkness like those long dead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has walled me in so I cannot escape; he has weighed me down with chains."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Even when I call out or cry for help, he shuts out my prayer."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has barred my way with blocks of stone; he has made my paths crooked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Like a bear lying in wait, like a lion in hiding,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "he dragged me from the path and mangled me and left me without help."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He drew his bow and made me the target for his arrows."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He pierced my heart with arrows from his quiver."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I became the laughingstock of all my people; they mock me in song all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has filled me with bitter herbs and given me gall to drink."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He has broken my teeth with gravel; he has trampled me in the dust."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I have been deprived of peace; I have forgotten what prosperity is."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "My splendor is gone and all that I had hoped from the Lord.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I remember my affliction and my wandering, the bitterness and the gall."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "I well remember them, and my soul is downcast within me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Yet this I call to mind and therefore I have hope:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Because of the Lord's great love we are not consumed, for his compassions never fail."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They are new every morning; great is your faithfulness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "The Lord is my portion; therefore I will wait for him.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Lord is good to those whose hope is in him, to the one who seeks him;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "it is good to wait quietly for the salvation of the Lord."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is good for a man to bear the yoke while he is young."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let him sit alone in silence, for the Lord has laid it on him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let him bury his face in the dust— there may yet be hope."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let him offer his cheek to one who would strike him, and let him be filled with disgrace."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For no one is cast off by the Lord forever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Though he brings grief, he will show compassion, so great is his unfailing love."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For he does not willingly bring affliction or grief to anyone."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "To crush underfoot all prisoners in the land,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 35,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to deny people their rights before the Most High,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 36,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "to deprive them of justice— would not the Lord see such things?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 37,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who can speak and have it happen if the Lord has not decreed it?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 38,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Is it not from the mouth of the Most High that both calamities and good things come?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Why should the living complain when punished for their sins?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let us examine our ways and test them, and let us return to the Lord."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let us lift up our hearts and our hands to God in heaven, and say:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 42,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "We have sinned and rebelled and you have not forgiven.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 43,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "You have covered yourself with anger and pursued us; you have slain without pity.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 44,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "You have covered yourself with a cloud so that no prayer can get through.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 45,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "You have made us scum and refuse among the nations.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 46,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "All our enemies have opened their mouths wide against us.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 47,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "We have suffered terror and pitfalls, ruin and destruction.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 48,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Streams of tears flow from my eyes because my people are destroyed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 49,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "My eyes will flow unceasingly, without relief,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 50,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "until the Lord looks down from heaven and sees."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 51,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "What I see brings grief to my soul because of all the women of my city."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 52,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Those who were my enemies without cause hunted me like a bird."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 53,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They tried to end my life in a pit and threw stones at me;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 54,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "the waters closed over my head, and I thought I was about to perish."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 55,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "I called on your name, Lord, from the depths of the pit.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 56,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "You heard my plea: 'Do not close your ears to my cry for relief.'",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 57,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Do not fear.",
          "speaker": "The Lord"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 58,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You, Lord, took up my case; you redeemed my life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 59,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Lord, you have seen the wrong done to me. Uphold my cause!",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 60,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "You have seen the depth of their vengeance, all their plots against me.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 61,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Lord, you have heard their insults, all their plots against me—",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 62,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "what my enemies whisper and mutter against me all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 63,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Look at them! Sitting or standing, they mock me in their songs."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 64,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Pay them back what they deserve, Lord, for what their hands have done.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 65,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Put a veil over their hearts, and may your curse be on them!",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 66,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Pursue them in anger and destroy them from under the heavens of the Lord.",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}